content: Had a long dinner with family. They're supportive but worried about my job loss. Assured them I'm on a path to recovery. The conversation sparked ideas for a more robust support system in my career.
Been working on a personal project to integrate AI into my trading strategies. The algorithm now can predict market movements with 60% accuracy. It's a start, but there's room for improvement.
Attended a finance tech conference. Met with several industry leaders, discussed potential job opportunities and the future of AI in finance. Left with a few promising leads.
Started a 3-day workshop on advanced trading algorithms. Day 1 was intense, covering high-frequency trading and market microstructure. Feeling overwhelmed but also eager to apply this knowledge.
Workshop day 3. Presented a project on an AI-driven trading strategy. Got feedback from industry experts. It was nerve-wracking but invaluable for my growth.
Took a break from the grind. Went to the Met with some new friends from the blockchain meetup. Art and tech have more in common than I thought—creativity and innovation at their core.
Back in the lab, refining my AI trading model. Integrated a new module for sentiment analysis from social media. The algorithm's accuracy jumped to 72%. Progress is slow but steady.
Had a breakthrough. My trading bot now incorporates real-time data feeds. Tested it during a live market simulation. It performed well, but there's always room for optimization.

Reflecting on the last 6 months, I've come a long way since losing my job. The city's energy fuels my ambition. Next up, exploring more opportunities in blockchain and AI, and strengthening my support network.
